# Signacare EMR — Docker build context excludes
#
# Phase R3 Azure dev/test deploy artifact (2026-04-30). Keeps Docker
# build context lean and prevents accidental inclusion of secrets,
# local-only configuration, and large directories that would bloat the
# image without contributing to runtime behaviour.

# Dependency directories — re-installed inside the image
node_modules
**/node_modules
**/node_modules/**

# Build outputs — Dockerfile builds from source (apps/web Dockerfile rebuilds Vite SPA; apps/api Dockerfile rebuilds tsc output)
**/dist
**/build
**/out
**/.next

# Test + coverage outputs
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output
**/*.lcov
**/node_modules

# Local environment files — secrets MUST come from Azure Key Vault, not baked in
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.production
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Local-only configuration
.claude
.cursor
.vscode
.idea
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store

# Git metadata — image doesn't need history
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github

# Logs + ephemeral state
**/*.log
**/logs
**/tmp
**/.cache

# Documentation + planning artifacts (not needed at runtime)
docs/archive
docs/quality
README.md
CLAUDE.md

# CI / development tooling
scripts/guards/__tests__
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx
e2e
playwright-report
test-results

# Package manager state files (re-derived on install)
**/.npm
**/.pnpm-store
**/.yarn

# Editor / OS artefacts
.history
*.bak
*~

# Existing local migrations directory mirror (kept in apps/api/migrations as Knex SoT)
apps/api/src/db/migrations/*.sql.bak

# Already-archived audit logs
docs/archive/auto-execute-logs
